        "Electronics contain valuable materials which can be recovered. Meanwhile, [@liuGlobalPerspectiveEwaste2023] reports e-waste is growing 3%-5% every year, globally. [@thukralExploratoryStudyProducer2023] identifies several barriers to e-waste management among producers including lack of awareness and infrastructure, attitudinal barriers, existing *informal* e-waste sector, and the need for an e-waste license.\n",
