        "[@buildersforclimateactionMakingRealZero2021] finds embodied carbon averages 250 kg CO₂-eq per m² of floor area for new Canadian homes, varying from 175-400 kg CO₂-eq per m² based on building material choices; one standard house emits 32–75 t CO₂-eq; the authors believe however, using *biogenic materials* (e.g. naturally grown materials including wood, bamboo, straw, hemp, cork, and mycelium), could make the houses carbon negative, storing 9–60 t CO₂-eq emissions - enough to meet the 2030 of the entire building sector.\n",
