        "Looking a the United Kingdom, [@harrissonAnalysisWhyUK2019] concludes UK's CO~2e~ emissions have fallen 43% from 1990 to 2017 through the use of less carbon-intensive energy sources and argues for moderate policies in [@hausfatherEmissionsBusinessUsual2020]."
